rComments: He was teaching the brain area of the pathophysiology which it was a heavy subject as the brain itself is a complicated organ in the body.  The lecture were interesting and boring as there was no activity throughout to see if we learned well or understood well the material.  Although, his notes are well organized.

I never listened to a lecture however I'd say the class is really well-organized and anatomy is a lot of independent learning. I appreciate the fact that all notes were in the ppt and the two midterms and homework were very fair. The final exam was not as challenging as it's made out to be but you really have to manage your time well to finish.

Amazing prof. His lectures are super slow. All of the midterm questions come directly from the slide notes that he provides. The notes are very easy to read and understand. The final however was completely different class avg went down from an A-/A to a D. Really focus on understanding the physiology of nervous system. Still recommend him

One of the most unaccommodating profs I've ever met. His classes are based on prerecorded lectures on youtube filmed in 2020.. Assignments were easy, first two midterms weren't that bad but the final exam was brutal.. Class average for the midterms and assignments were in the 90's but the exam average was a D.. Oh and he talks so slow. Good luck..
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: The lectures were okay but they can take a long time since he only speaks over slides(diagrams), which forces you to write down everything he says which can be good to get it into your head. Otherwise, I found I studied pretty much everything there was to know and I found the exams to be quite difficult. Read the textbook for a fuller understanding

Dr Fortier is amazing! The midterm content is exactly as how it appears in the notes he provides, so simple memorization is all you need to do! The assignments are fairly easy as well. The final exam was quite difficult because it's on physiology which you need to understand more than memorize. Interesting course and content, loved it!

Maybe it was because it was an online course, but it was boring watching 30-50 mins videos on anatomy, and would much recommend taking it in person if you can. The professor is good at explaining the concepts in the videos and you will not have much difficulty trying to understand the content. Class itself is content-heavy thus study in advance!
I didn't go to class, and got an A+, I just read the slide notes. The exam was straightforward, and pretty easy if you studied even a little bit.

Solid professor. I didn't really like the style of the notes and slides, so I would definitely recommend reformatting them. Some of the content is a little dated and needs to be updated. All in all, good prof and fun course.

Not too bad of a prof. The exam is challenging but fair. Definitely have to speed up the lectures but that is a minor complaint. The examples provided in lectures are memorable which helped with studying. You have to study lots though if you want to get a good grade

He's alright, test questions tricky, but you can get by just by memorising his notes with no need for the diagrams or watching his lectures. He prepares his notes all in one shot, which is kinda nice & if you watch the lectures, do speed him up to 1.5 or 2 & it'll feel as if he speaks normally. Best of luck :)

One of the most memorable profs to have in your college career. His exam was very straightforward and the questions can be answered from the notes he has under each slide. just study those and you will be fine for the exams. Amazing lectures and explains stuff very well

His videos he talks really slow, but that's a minor complaint since you can speed him up. Explains concepts well. His exam questions came from the notes he provides. Overall, he had the easiest PHS chapter but that could just be due to the fact we've reviewed neuro things every years. content is pretty simple too

Dr. Fortier's lectures are quite boring as he talks very slowly. However, they are not mandatory to attend. He gives out a package with 130 pages and my advice is to make each sentence into point form and make cue cards out of them. Watch some extra videos to better understand the concepts. The exam was pretty straight forward.

He is super intelligent and so he explains concepts super well. His notes are super organized. All you have to do in class is listen, there is nothing else you can ask for from an anatomy prof. Would definitely take again

Lectures were quite boring and hard to pay attention to . Since he provides ALL the notes for his part of the course, attendance isn't completely necessary but study at your own risk. His final is harder than he makes it seem because it is knowledge based not just memorizing.

Hard to pay attention to lectures- they are slow & boring, but he knows what he is talking about and explains concepts really well. No need to take notes/ show up to class. Final is only composed of material covered in his slideshows. If you study(which i didnt) you will do well. His questions were "which answer is false" which can be really hard.

He's very nice and gives you all the notes you need for the final. And if you really memorize them, you can get a good grade. Didn't pay much attention in class since he said info that wasnt needed for the final. The harder topics, he explains them well and you can always find youtube videos that explain the topics properly.

Exam is based 100% off of the single powerpoint of notes he gives (exam questions are straight forward MCQs with a bit of thinking), don't need to bother going to class. Reformat the powerpoint to bullet form, spend 2 or 3 days memorizing all of the notes, and you'll do well on the exam.

Dr. Fortnier provides his students with notes, letting them know that only the notes will be tested, as anything extra that is said in lectures is supplementary to complement and make the notes easier to remember. I had always struggled with anatomy previously (50-60%'s), but with Dr. Fortnier, I managed to get a 65% on the final, which is awesome.
His lectures are very boring. You just need to focus on the notes under his slides. Exams are based off those notes.

Prof Fortier did the neurophysiology part of my ANP1106. He gave a huge booklet with all the notes at the beginning of the year so if you miss class it is not a big deal. His lectures are quite dry but he uses images to help with the understanding part. Super nice and approachable prof but quite heavy exam as it is a lot of "which one is false".

I had him as a prof for the neurophysiology portion of ANP1106 and definitely liked him as a prof. He uploads one giant powerpoint with only pictures but you need to know all of his notes. I thought I wouldn't like his way of teaching but it actually helped me. He is a nice guy and tries to give lots of relatable examples to help understand concept

Dr. Fortier's way of explaining is perfect! Best anatomy professor I've had so far because of his clarity and notes. Attendance is mandatory, especially since his notes are big paragraphs and not bulleted on his PowerPoint slides. All in all, a great professor!

Professor Fortier was a great ANP professor! His notes are all together in one pdf which makes it easy to study. Very clear and interesting to listen to! Also has a great sense of humor, overall really great prof! Highly recommended

He gives you 1 powerpoint before the first class with ALL the lecture notes in there. Exam is based 100% off his powerpoint, and although his slides come with paragraphs of notes, all you need to do is copy-paste it into a word document, format it into bullet points, and go to class. Follow that and you'll ace his section no problem.

Worst prof in university so far. Takes a simple interesting concept and makes it 1) boring, 2) complex 3) unclear. Is not committed to his students (will not meet with them). Has no clue how to teach and interact with students. Not a friendly personality. I would strongly advise to change classes especially if you like neuroscience.
Awful slides to work through. Class will put you to sleep

He is a nice prof, but his teaching is extremely boring. It was a pain to sit through his lectures. Also, his slides were a diagram, and then a paragraph long explanation, rather than point form. Pain to read and pick out important pieces of info. Exam questions were mostly "which one of these statements is false" etc. Read textbook for an A!
Very clear and concise with his teaching.
Decent prof. His notes are pure gold because all exam questions are based on them. Reasonable clarity during lectures but he is rather monotonous and boring. His exam questions were pretty hard.

He's a lovely prof and a nice guy. A little dry, but he gives the entire class notes for his section right at the beginning of the semester. Read them over; the notes are clear and concise. His assignments and exams are a bit tough but you have the notes to read over the semester so don't fall behind and you'll be golden.

At first I found this prof boring but he definitely grows on you! He's clearly into what he's teaching and has good anecdotes too that are usually funny. It's a specific sense of humour, but it makes the material stick more easily. I'd recommend him, he knows his stuff!!
Le prof explique très bien. Le cours peut être dûr, mais si on étudie très fort vous n'aurez de difficulté. C'est note de cours sont très très clair.

He is by far the best prof for this course. He can be kind of dry sometimes, but has a strange nerdy sence of humor about him. He explains things very well, and his notes are well organized. I would definatly take another course with him.
He`s not bad. The exam are not tricky but are based on understanding so it`s hard. He`s definitely a good teacher!
You have to think.. That's why some people don't like him(they don't like to think, they like easy answer :-( ). Greate prof and know his stuff!
Teacher model
HARD TEACHER FOR AN ANATOMY CLASS. probably because for his questions you actually needed to think.
No Comments
YAWN... what a boring prof! you need to concentrate in this class because it's not easy, but he makes it very hard not to fall asleep...
Like as if anatomy wasn't hard enough...makes the students fall asleep (those who actually show up to class).
